Step 1) Pick a race and choose one racial trait

Step 2) Attributes

When creating a character you are given 18 point to allocate across these 4 attributes.
Each attribute starts off with an 8 and increasing it by 1 costs 1 point until you hit 13.
Increasıng it from 13 to 14 and onwards costs 2 points per 1 until you hit 16.
Increasing it from 16 to 17 and onwards costs 3 points per 1.
At the end you will increase one attribute by 1 point according to your racial bonus.

Any stat that is within 2 points of your highest stat is called a primary stat.
According to your specific combination of primary stats you will gain an archetype and and archetype trait associated with it.

Step 3) Pick a background

Step 4) Pick 2 skills of your choice to be trained in or 1 skill to be skilled in.

Step 5) Buy Equipment from the list of starting equipments with your starting money.

Step 6) Set up your Health, Speed, Evasiveness, Initiative, Damage Reduction, Stress Threshold and number of spells then choose or make your own abilities as many as you are allowed to have.

Step 7) Completely optional set up a personality


